rComments: Shely is an excellent professor. She was open to student needs, feedback and ensured needs were met. I was happy to see she incorporated feedback provided during the mid term since most professors only ask because they are mandated to do so, but don't really make changes. Shely was a fair grader and provided lots of helpful comments.
Shely is great at constructive feedback, she encourages students to participate in simulated role plays and class discussion. I feel that I learned a lot from this course thanks to Shely.
